IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO ENGAGE OUR ALUMNI IN ACTIVITIES THAT WILL ADVANCE UTSA AS A TOP-TIER INSTITUTION.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO ENGAGE OUR ALUMNI IN ACTIVITIES THAT WILL ADVANCE UTSA AS A TOP-TIER INSTITUTION. OUR FOCUS IS TO DELIVER VALUE-ADDED SERVICES AND EVENTS WHERE OUR ALUMNI CAN CONNECT WITH EACH OTHER, WITH CURRENT STUDENTS AND/OR WITH THE UNIVERSITY. WE INVEST IN PROGRAMS THAT ENABLE ACCESSIBILITY TO HIGHER EDUCATION AND SUPPORT LOCAL COMMUNITY EDUCATIONAL INITIATIVES. IN DOING SO, WE STRIVE TO CREATE A SENSE OF PRIDE, PURPOSE AND PHILANTHROPY THAT IS THE ESSENCE OF THE UTSA ALUMNI ASSOCIATION MEMBERSHIP EXPERIENCE.
IRS990.Desc: ALUMNI RELATIONS: UTSA ALUMNI ASSOCIATION IS A MEMBERSHIP ORGANIZATION THAT PROVIDES SERVICES, PROGRAMS AND EVENTS TO INVOLVE ALUMNI, TO SUPPORT THE EDUCATIONAL ACTIVITIES OF THE UNIVERSITY, AND TO SUPPORT POLICIES GENERALLY FAVORABLE TO HIGHER EDUCATION. ALUMNI PROGRAMS ARE DESIGNED TO CONNECT AND BUILD RELATIONSHIPS BETWEEN ALUMNI, CURRENT STUDENTS, THE UTSA ALUMNI ASSOCIATION AND THE UNIVERSITY OF TEXAS AT SAN ANTONIO.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: STUDENT RELATIONS: PROVIDES SCHOLARSHIPS FOR UNIVERSITY OF TEXAS AT SAN ANTONIO STUDENTS WHO DEMONSTRATE SCHOLASTIC PROMISE AND PARTICIPATE IN COMMUNITY ACTIVITIES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: COMMUNITY AND UNIVERSITY RELATIONS: THESE PROGRAMS ARE DESIGNED TO FOSTER SUPPORT WITH THE SAN ANTONIO AND UTSA COMMUNITY, TO INCLUDE THOSE OUTSIDE THE ALUMNI BASE. THIS INCLUDES BEING INVOLVED WITH OTHER GROUPS THROUGH ATTENDANCE AND PARTICIPATION IN VARIOUS UNIVERSITY AND COMMUNITY EVENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE INTENDED TO BE USED TO PROVIDE SCHOLARSHIPS.
THE ALUMNI ASSOCIATION HAS A SCHOLARSHIP COMMITTEE IN PLACE TO DETERMINE WHO SHOULD RECEIVE SCHOLARSHIPS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FOLLOWING PERSONS SHALL BE ELIGIBLE TO BECOME MEMBERS OF THE ASSOCIATION: GRADUATES OF, CURRENT OR FORMER STUDENTS OF UTSA; RECIPIENTS OF AN HONORARY DEGREE CONFERRED BY UTSA;PERSONS ELECTED TO HONORARY MEMBERSHIP BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS PURSUANT TO SECTION 203;AND ANY OTHER PERSON WHO IS A FRIEND OF THE UNIVERSITY, AND REQUESTS MEMBERSHIP PURSUANT TO SECTION 204.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH ACTIVE MEMBER PRESENT AT THE ANNUAL MEETING WHERE BOARD MEMBERS ARE ELECTED ARE ENTITLED TO ONE VOTE ON THE ELECTION OF THE BOARD MEMBERS. VOTING BY PROXY SHALL NOT BE PERMITTED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH ACTIVE MEMBER PRESENT AT ANY MEETING OF THE ASSOCIATION AT WHICH A QUORUM IS PRESENT SHALL BE ENTITLED TO ONE VOTE ON ALL MATTERS SUBMITTED TO A VOTE AT SUCH MEETING. VOTING BY PROXY SHALL NOT BE PERMITTED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 FEDERAL INCOME TAX RETURN IS PREPARED BY THE ORGANIZATION'S INDEPENDENT CERTIFIED PUBLIC ACCOUNTANTS. IT IS REVIEWED BY THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, TREASURER, THE EXECUTIVE AND FINANCE COMMITTES OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTOR'S BEFORE BEING SIGNED AND FILED WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD REVIEWS AND SUBMITS CONFLICT OF INTEREST DECLARATIONS ANNUALLY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: SINCE THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT HAVE EMPLOYEES, THE PROCESS OF DETERMINING COMPENSATION IS NOT NEEDED. THE AMOUNTS LISTED AS SALARIES AND BENEFITS ARE REIMBURSEMENTS TO THE UNIVERSITY FOR THE USE OF UNIVERSITY EMPLOYEES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COPIES OF THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.
